snippet.textDisplay: Excellent music and execution. I do love Mohiner Ghoraguli and I have immense respect for the musical contribution they have on bangla music. But I have an observation regarding these collaborative efforts. Mohiner ghoraguli is basically indian bangla song whereas Tuhin bhai has his own good music and also from Bangladesh we have legendary songs and singers. Why shouldn't we focus on those before going to indian bangla music? We are just in the 3rd season, not like 15th season of coke studio pakistan. And regarding latinas and foreigners in the music videos to make it more commercial is just a cheap marketing stunt. Our musicians can do that too, why do you have to bring in foreigners?
